                            <comment id="142384" author="lokesh.jaliminche" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2016 07:47:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On cleanup racer terminates child scripts: file_create.sh, dir_create.sh, etc. Children of those srcipts do not get terminated&lt;br/&gt;
that way. Long running commands, like dd, causes annoying warnings: /mnt/lustre2 is still busy, wait one second&lt;br/&gt;
on attempt to umount $DIR2.&lt;br/&gt;
Added  trap to all child scripts to have them to cleanup on exiting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
